    <h1>
        Phosphorus-doped Monocrystalline Silicon Boule
    </h1>
    <h3>
        Source
    </h3>
    <text><style color="0xaaaaaa" italic="true">Note: this page is ported from MCMOD's GTCEu wiki.<br/>Author: <style color="0xa4e7ff" hover-info="url" underlined="true" url-link="https://center.mcmod.cn/179043/">花海</style>, <style color="0xa4e7ff" hover-info="url" underlined="true" url-link="https://github.com/Yefancy">KilaBash</style><br/></style></text>
    <text>
        A Phosphorus-doped monocrystalline silicon boule is produced by smelting 64 <style color="0xbbffaa">silicon dusts</style> and 8 <style color="0xbbffaa">phosphorus dusts</style> with a small pile of gallium arsenide dust in an <style color="0xafff00" underlined="true" link="gtceu:multiblock/electric_blast_furnace" hover-info="click link">Electric Blast Furnace</style>,
        which requires an additional nitrogen feed, and the smelting needs to be carried out at a minimum coil temperature of <style color="0xff5555">2,484 K</style>, utilising the Kanthal Coil for smelting. 
    </text>
    <recipe id="gtceu:electric_blast_furnace/phosphorus_boule"/>
    <br/>
    <text>
        One phosphorus-doped monocrystalline silicon boule can be cut into 32 <style color="0xafff00" underlined="true" link="gtceu:circuits/phosphorus_wafer" hover-info="click link">phosphorus-doped wafers</style> in a <style color="0xafff00" underlined="true" link="gtceu:machines/cutter" hover-info="click link">cutter</style>, a process that also requires a minimum HV-Tier of voltage.
    </text>
    <recipe id="gtceu:cutter/cut_phosphorus_boule_water"/>
    <br/>
</page>
       